---
title: Homepage
permalink: /
---

{% extends '@theme/_layouts/base.html.twig' %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="container">
        <div class="text-center mb-5">
            <p class="text-3 mb-0">Building static websites, your way</p>
            <p>...yet another static website generator</p>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-8 mx-auto mb-5">
                <div class="c-terminal">
                    <div class="c-terminal__header">
                        <span class="c-terminal__circle c-terminal__circle--red"></span>
                        <span class="c-terminal__circle c-terminal__circle--yellow"></span>
                        <span class="c-terminal__circle c-terminal__circle--green"></span>
                    </div>

                    <div class="c-terminal__body">
                        {% markdown %}
                        ```yaml
                        ---
                        title: Quick Intro
                        slug: What can stakx do out of the box?
                        permalink: /blog/
                        ---
                        ```

                        ```twig
                        {% raw %}
                        {% extends "@theme/layouts/base.html.twig" %}

                        {% block content %}
                            {% for post in collections.posts | order('date', 'DESC') %}
                                <article>
                                    <h2>
                                        <a href="{{ url(post) }}">{{ post.title }}</a>
                                    </h2>
                                    <p class="text-muted">
                                        <strong>{{ post.date | date('F d, Y') }}</strong>
                                    </p>
                                </article>
                            {% endfor %}
                        {% endblock %}
                        {% endraw %}
                        ```
                        {% endmarkdown %}
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="u-background u-background--lpurple">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row py-5">
                <div class="col-md-3 text-center mb-3 mb-md-0">
                    <img src="{{ url('assets/images/logo-twig.png') }}" alt="Twig template engine logo">
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-9">
                    <h2 class="mt-0 u-text--light-purple">Made for those with a PHP background</h2>
                    <p><strong>Fast:</strong> Twig compiles templates down to plain optimized PHP code. The overhead compared to regular PHP code was reduced to the very minimum.</p>
                    <p><strong>Secure:</strong> Twig has a sandbox mode to evaluate untrusted template code. This allows Twig to be used as a template language for applications where users may modify the template design.</p>
                    <p><strong>Flexible:</strong> Twig is powered by a flexible lexer and parser. This allows the developer to define its own custom tags and filters, and create its own DSL.</p>
                    <p>&mdash; Twig</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
